<%= render layout: 'shared/blog/layout' do %>
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
      <p class="text-xl dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I'm excited to announce the release of <a href="https://sprintflint.com" target="_blank" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 underline">SprintFlint</a>—a simple sprint ticketing tool built to help agile teams understand their velocity and ship on time.
      </p>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        SprintFlint answers one question clearly: <strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">"Will we finish this sprint on time?"</strong> That question drives everything about the product.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-white text-slate-900 mb-4">Why I Built It</h2>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        I built SprintFlint because Linear complicated things over time. What started as a clean tool became difficult to work with—the route to even view a kanban board got convoluted, and they don't provide the in-depth velocity analysis that teams actually need to hit deadlines.
      </p>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        I wanted something focused—a tool that tracks velocity, shows progress against plan, and alerts you when you're falling behind. No feature bloat, just the metrics that matter.
      </p>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        SprintFlint is purpose-built for agile teams with a clear hierarchy: Organisations → Projects → Sprints → Tickets. Each level provides the analytics you need to understand where you stand.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-white text-slate-900 mb-4">Key Features</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-400 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">Velocity Analytics</strong>—Track story points completed per sprint, see completion rates, and use historical data to plan realistic future sprints.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-400 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">Kanban Board</strong>—Click and drag to scroll horizontally across your sprint board. Drag tickets between columns to update status instantly.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-400 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">Real-Time Progress</strong>—Watch sprint progress live with forecast vs expected completion charts. Automatic alerts keep sprint leads informed.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-400 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">Real-Time Collaboration</strong>—When someone moves an issue or updates a status, the whole team sees it instantly.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-400 mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
          </svg>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">Global Search</strong>—Press ⌘K to search across your entire organisation quickly.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-white text-slate-900 mb-4">Built With Rails and Hotwire</h2>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        SprintFlint is built on Rails 8.1 with Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus), delivering real-time updates without the complexity of heavy JavaScript frameworks. The backend runs on Ruby 3.4 with PostgreSQL, Redis, and Sidekiq for background jobs.
      </p>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Every interaction is designed for speed—from magic link authentication to drag-to-scroll kanban navigation. Less time in the tool means more time shipping.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="apple-glass p-8 md:p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-white text-slate-900 mb-4">What's Coming Next</h2>
      <p class="dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The roadmap includes AI-powered features to help teams write better tickets and resolve issues faster:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 dark:text-slate-400 text-slate-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-2">→</span>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">AI Ticket Writer</strong>—Generate well-structured user stories and tickets with AI assistance.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-2">→</span>
          <span><strong class="dark:text-white text-slate-900">AI Issue Investigation</strong>—Cross-reference similar issues from GitHub, find past solutions and related discussions.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-2">→</span>
